<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,489,1290,1349]" box="[151,441,1325,1349]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
(
<figureCitation box="[158,260,1325,1349]" captionStart="PLATE 4" captionStartId="44.[151,229,1945,1966]" captionTargetBox="[210,1384,172,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-88@44.[197,1396,159,1930]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="PLATE 4. A–I. General habitus. (A) Dialodia longilobata, sp. nov.; (B) Dialodia bispinata, sp. nov.; (C) Dialodia bilongata, sp. nov.; (D) Dialodia brevisetacea, sp. nov.; (E) Dialodia aviculobata, sp. nov.; (F) Evansolidia setacea, sp. nov.; (G) Evansolidia episetacea, sp. nov.; (H) Evansolidia inflata, sp. nov.; (I) Evansolidia gracilitas, sp. nov." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Plate 4D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[271,433,1325,1349]" captionStart="FIGURES" captionStartId="76.[151,259,1770,1791]" captionTargetBox="[273,1332,229,1751]" captionTargetId="figure-71@76.[224,1381,197,1898]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="FIGURES. 226–233. Evansolidia inflata, sp. nov. (226) male pygofer, lateral view; (227) left subgenital plate, ventral view; (228) right style, lateral view; (229) right style, dorsal view; (230) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (231) aedeagus, ventral view; (232) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (233) connective, caudal view." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Figs. 226–233</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,1390,2026]" box="[151,797,1390,1415]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,243,1391,1415]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" reason="1">Length.</emphasis>
Male 6.50 mm (estimated—specimen damaged).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,1390,2026]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,462,1427,1451]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" reason="1">External morphology.</emphasis>
Medium size, robust species. General color black with yellow markings. Forewing black with translucent transverse, broad bands; mesonotum black with yellow markings; pronotum black with yellow broken band on anterior margin, broken, transverse, submarginal yellow line on posterior margin; crown black, longitudinal yellow stripe medially and next to eyes, face black; clypeus with broad longitudinal yellow stripe medially and laterally extending nearly to apex of clypellus (
<figureCitation box="[857,963,1570,1594]" captionStart="PLATE 4" captionStartId="44.[151,229,1945,1966]" captionTargetBox="[210,1384,172,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-88@44.[197,1396,159,1930]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="PLATE 4. A–I. General habitus. (A) Dialodia longilobata, sp. nov.; (B) Dialodia bispinata, sp. nov.; (C) Dialodia bilongata, sp. nov.; (D) Dialodia brevisetacea, sp. nov.; (E) Dialodia aviculobata, sp. nov.; (F) Evansolidia setacea, sp. nov.; (G) Evansolidia episetacea, sp. nov.; (H) Evansolidia inflata, sp. nov.; (I) Evansolidia gracilitas, sp. nov." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Plate 4D</figureCitation>
). Head narrower than pronotum, anterior margin obtusely angulate; crown broad, nearly as wide as width of eyes, produced distally about ¼ entire length, lateral margins convergent basally, slightly elevated; eyes large, semiglobular; pronotum slightly longer than median length of crown; mesonotum large, about twice as long as pronotum; forewings typical; clypeus long, broad, lateral margins broadly convex, broader basally than apically; clypellus broad, inflated basally, lateral margins constricted medially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,1390,2026]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,380,1786,1811]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" reason="1">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view with small triangulate lobe on caudodorsal margin, glabrous (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES" captionStartId="76.[151,259,1770,1791]" captionTargetBox="[273,1332,229,1751]" captionTargetId="figure-71@76.[224,1381,197,1898]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="FIGURES. 226–233. Evansolidia inflata, sp. nov. (226) male pygofer, lateral view; (227) left subgenital plate, ventral view; (228) right style, lateral view; (229) right style, dorsal view; (230) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (231) aedeagus, ventral view; (232) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (233) connective, caudal view." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 226</figureCitation>
); left subgenital plate long, narrow, glabrous (
<figureCitation box="[728,830,1822,1846]" captionStart="FIGURES" captionStartId="76.[151,259,1770,1791]" captionTargetBox="[273,1332,229,1751]" captionTargetId="figure-71@76.[224,1381,197,1898]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="FIGURES. 226–233. Evansolidia inflata, sp. nov. (226) male pygofer, lateral view; (227) left subgenital plate, ventral view; (228) right style, lateral view; (229) right style, dorsal view; (230) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (231) aedeagus, ventral view; (232) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (233) connective, caudal view." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 227</figureCitation>
); style robust, shorter than aedeagus, apophysis with outer lateral margin broadly expanded medially in lateral view, small digitate lobe distally (
<figureCitation box="[1177,1343,1858,1882]" captionStart="FIGURES" captionStartId="76.[151,259,1770,1791]" captionTargetBox="[273,1332,229,1751]" captionTargetId="figure-71@76.[224,1381,197,1898]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="FIGURES. 226–233. Evansolidia inflata, sp. nov. (226) male pygofer, lateral view; (227) left subgenital plate, ventral view; (228) right style, lateral view; (229) right style, dorsal view; (230) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (231) aedeagus, ventral view; (232) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (233) connective, caudal view." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Figs. 228, 229</figureCitation>
); aedeagus in lateral view expanded subbasally, narrowed distally, in dorsal view narrow, tubular throughout, 3 processes on dorsal margin, 2 subbasally, l medially, gonopore near middle, exiting dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[1119,1291,1930,1954]" captionStart="FIGURES" captionStartId="76.[151,259,1770,1791]" captionTargetBox="[273,1332,229,1751]" captionTargetId="figure-71@76.[224,1381,197,1898]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="FIGURES. 226–233. Evansolidia inflata, sp. nov. (226) male pygofer, lateral view; (227) left subgenital plate, ventral view; (228) right style, lateral view; (229) right style, dorsal view; (230) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (231) aedeagus, ventral view; (232) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (233) connective, caudal view." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Figs. 230, 231</figureCitation>
); connective broadly Y-shaped, membranous on each side of middle, stem very short (
<figureCitation box="[966,1065,1966,1990]" captionStart="FIGURES" captionStartId="76.[151,259,1770,1791]" captionTargetBox="[273,1332,229,1751]" captionTargetId="figure-71@76.[224,1381,197,1898]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="FIGURES. 226–233. Evansolidia inflata, sp. nov. (226) male pygofer, lateral view; (227) left subgenital plate, ventral view; (228) right style, lateral view; (229) right style, dorsal view; (230) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (231) aedeagus, ventral view; (232) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (233) connective, caudal view." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 232</figureCitation>
); dorsal connective long, narrow, broad basally, slightly bifurcate basally (
<figureCitation box="[605,703,2002,2026]" captionStart="FIGURES" captionStartId="76.[151,259,1770,1791]" captionTargetBox="[273,1332,229,1751]" captionTargetId="figure-71@76.[224,1381,197,1898]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="FIGURES. 226–233. Evansolidia inflata, sp. nov. (226) male pygofer, lateral view; (227) left subgenital plate, ventral view; (228) right style, lateral view; (229) right style, dorsal view; (230) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (231) aedeagus, ventral view; (232) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (233) connective, caudal view." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 233</figureCitation>
), attached to base of aedeagal socle (
<figureCitation box="[1117,1216,2002,2026]" captionStart="FIGURES" captionStartId="76.[151,259,1770,1791]" captionTargetBox="[273,1332,229,1751]" captionTargetId="figure-71@76.[224,1381,197,1898]" captionTargetPageId="76" captionText="FIGURES. 226–233. Evansolidia inflata, sp. nov. (226) male pygofer, lateral view; (227) left subgenital plate, ventral view; (228) right style, lateral view; (229) right style, dorsal view; (230) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (231) aedeagus, ventral view; (232) dorsal connective, dorsal view; (233) connective, caudal view." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 230</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
