<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,151,356]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,224,248]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of this species is descriptive for the aedeagus which has a unique, medially inflated shaft in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,151,356]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,296,320]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from all known members of the genus for its unique, medially inflated aedeagus.
</paragraph>
